This project uses the following open-source packages:

1. sentence-transformers (Apache License 2.0)
   - https://github.com/UKPLab/sentence-transformers
   - Used for SBERT embeddings (all-MiniLM-L6-v2 model)

2. PyTorch (BSD License)
   - https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch
   - Deep learning backend for embeddings

3. Streamlit (Apache License 2.0)
   - https://github.com/streamlit/streamlit
   - Interactive web application framework

4. numpy (BSD License)
   - https://github.com/numpy/numpy
   - Numerical computations

5. pydantic (MIT License)
   - https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic
   - Data validation and parsing

6. pytest (MIT License)
   - https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest
   - Testing framework

See requirements.txt for version details.

---

CORPUS ATTRIBUTION:

The Pure Meanings corpus (data/intents.json) includes examples based on:
- General NLU conventions
- Voice assistant paradigms
- Polysemic examples from linguistic literature

These are original examples created for demonstration purposes.

